00:21:08.130 --> 00:21:15.690
that's all about, you know, terrible, drunken,
mad cap antics. But, I find it a little bit

00:21:15.690 --> 00:21:21.250
depressing. You know, I find, I find when
I walk past a gym in any city, I look through

00:21:21.250 --> 00:21:27.600
the window and I see ranks and ranks of people
on treadmills with their ear buds in, watching

00:21:27.600 --> 00:21:30.211
Fox News or CNN or ESPN, and going like this

00:21:30.211 --> 00:21:31.330
[footsteps]

00:21:31.330 --> 00:21:35.470
I, I just, you know, it's almost s-, like
a suicidal; makes me feel almost suicidal.

00:21:35.470 --> 00:21:39.130
The, and it's kinda, you know

00:21:39.130 --> 00:21:40.130
[sighs]

00:21:40.130 --> 00:21:45.800
you know, sports are sport or athletic activity,
one thing that is an underappreciated thing

00:21:45.800 --> 00:21:51.871
about it, is it's kind of funny. Like, at
least at the level that I do it, the level,

00:21:51.871 --> 00:21:57.410
a lot of people do sports on, it's like, it's
