00:26:17.410 --> 00:26:18.410
the dilution--

00:26:18.410 --> 00:26:19.410
&gt;&gt;Zach: Oh, absolutely, yeah.

00:26:19.410 --> 00:26:24.030
&gt;&gt;memberfemale4: so what is kinda your, I
guess, opinion on kinda what is that fine

00:26:24.030 --> 00:26:28.650
line having media be a good thing to kind
of bring exposure to all these sports, but

00:26:28.650 --> 00:26:32.760
then also media being part of the, the problem
in diluting the--

00:26:32.760 --> 00:26:37.660
&gt;&gt;Zach: Well, I think roller derby is an interesting
example of a sport that is confronting this

00:26:37.660 --> 00:26:41.230
issue right now. I mean, roller derby has
gotten a tremendous, since roller derby was

00:26:41.230 --> 00:26:46.690
revived less than a decade ago, it's very
serious, but also, it's an interesting thing.

00:26:46.690 --> 00:26:51.990
It's seriously competitive; it has a frivolous
sort of image of women in tight outfits with

00:26:51.990 --> 00:26:55.120
weird names, fighting each other on a track
and bands playing at half-time and everybody

00:26:55.120 --> 00:27:02.860
getting really drunk. But, it has also spawned
this incredible proliferation of national

00:27:02.860 --> 00:27:06.150
leagues, or teams, city leagues around the
country and then national competition and

00:27:06.150 --> 00:27:08.510
very serious tournaments.

00:27:08.510 --> 00:27:13.630
And yet, most of the media attraction it has
intent-, it has attracted has focused on the

00:27:13.630 --> 00:27:18.260
sort of superficial side of its appeal, which
is these kind of rock and roll chicks who

00:27:18.260 --> 00:27:23.450
like to fight and beat each other up. They
don't ever, the media coverage rarely delves

00:27:23.450 --> 00:27:27.481
into the seriousness and the sort of, the
intense nature of the sport. I mean, if you

00:27:27.481 --> 00:27:32.370
watch two of the top roller derby teams in
the country go at it with something on the

00:27:32.370 --> 00:27:37.140
line, it's as intense as anything you can
imagine. It's like the Yankees and Red Sox

00:27:37.140 --> 00:27:41.390
in the seventh game of the LCS or something.
I mean, it's just the animosity, the tactics,

00:27:41.390 --> 00:27:45.750
the speed, the strength, the damage, the bruising.

00:27:45.750 --> 00:27:51.180
So, here's a sport that's obviously found
some sort of unlooked for, unexpected national

00:27:51.180 --> 00:27:55.790
success. It's attracted a fair amount of media
attention. There's a Drew Barrymore movie

00:27:55.790 --> 00:28:00.990
which I actually thought was pretty good,
I was pleasantly surprised I guess I would

00:28:00.990 --> 00:28:07.100
say. But yet, what is really, what I found
really special about it, which is the, this

00:28:07.100 --> 00:28:11.811
sort of grass roots manifestation of sports
for that basically attracts people that were

00:28:11.811 --> 00:28:17.460
never involved in sports before, it kind of
gets pushed to the wayside. And they're definitely

00:28:17.460 --> 00:28:22.030
wrestling with, with what sort of television
coverage they want, what kind of media coverage

00:28:22.030 --> 00:28:28.510
they think is appropriate, what sort of level
of sponsorship or involvement with outside

00:28:28.510 --> 00:28:34.390
financing they can deal with while continuing
to maintain control of the sport at sort of

00:28:34.390 --> 00:28:38.391
grass roots nature. So I think that there
comes a point where it's a fine line.

00:28:38.391 --> 00:28:42.820
I mean, you know, I don't think that, I don't
think the guys at the Trans Iowa really need

00:28:42.820 --> 00:28:48.930
to worry about this issue so much, but I think
that, you know, when something like roller

00:28:48.930 --> 00:28:52.780
derby or bike polo, which is another sport
that's gone from being, you know, a scrappy

00:28:52.780 --> 00:28:58.230
sportplayed by about 15 people around the
country, to having a very recognizable core

00:28:58.230 --> 00:29:01.221
of national or international support. Eventually,
it gets to the point where you have to say,

00:29:01.221 --> 00:29:06.450
"Well, what's going to happen to our sport?
Is it going to become just another part of

00:29:06.450 --> 00:29:13.660
the sort of mainstream sports or alternative
sports or extreme sports spectrum, where TV

00:29:13.660 --> 00:29:19.150
and corporate sponsorship play a role? Or
do we keep it, or do our best to keep it underground?"

00:29:19.150 --> 00:29:22.480
I don't know if there's a right answer to
that question, but there's certainly a time

00:29:22.480 --> 00:29:28.110
when a line is crossed. And I think it's about
the time when a player cashes the first check

00:29:28.110 --> 00:29:29.110
from Red Bull.

00:29:29.110 --> 00:29:39.560
Anything else? All right, seeing none. Thanks
very much and thanks a lot.

